│ responsible. It correctly identifies the "is power of two"   │
│ pattern but fails to consider the full implications of       │
│ removing the `x != 0` check.                                 │
│                                                              │
│ By removing the guard, the `ctpop` intrinsic is evaluated    │
│ unconditionally. The transformation is only valid if it can  │
│ be proven that the input to `ctpop` is never zero. The       │
│ `range(1, 33)` metadata implies this, but the transform      │
│ itself leads to a state where this assumption is violated if │
│ the guard is removed without further checks.                 │
